<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">Detailed itinerary (Basel-Amsterdam)</h2>
<p>CRUISE Basel - Strasbourg - Speyer - Mannheim/Heidelberg - Rüdesheim - Koblenz - Cochem - Cologne - Volendam - Amsterdam</p>
<p><br /><strong>Day 1</strong> </p>
<p>Fly to Basel, transfer to Basel port and board your AMADEUS ship in the late afternoon for an early evening departure. After first scenic impressions of the Rhine, there’ll be a welcome cocktail party before dinner is served on board.</p>
<p><strong>Day 2</strong> </p>
<p>Today you arrive in the picturesque French wine region of Alsace, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The ship docks in Strasbourg where you can join a guided city tour*. </p>
<p><strong>Day 3</strong> </p>
<p>The ship arrives in Speyer* (optional city walk), an old imperial city on the Rhine. In the afternoon the ship docks in Mannheim where you can join a coach excursion to Heidelberg*.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4</strong> </p>
<p>Today you arrive in the charming old wine town of Rüdesheim* with its long narrow street lined with wine taverns, shops and restaurants, the Drosselgasse. The optional city walk includes a visit to the music museum. Later enjoy the cruise along probably the most famous and scenic stretch of the Rhine valley, passing hilltop castles, terraced vineyards and attractive waterside villages for 65 delightful kilometers. During the afternoon the ship skirts round the famous 132-metre Lorelei Rock, icon of this great river. In the afternoon you arrive at Koblenz* (optional city walk), a 2000-year old town at the junction of the rivers Rhine and Moselle, where picturesque riverside scenery meets an abundance of cultural monuments and historic buildings.</p>
<p><strong>Day 5</strong> </p>
<p>The ship arrives in Cochem* at midday. Explore this quaint medieval town on your own or take a guided walk* which includes a wine tasting.</p>
<p><strong>Day 6</strong> </p>
<p>The ship reaches the Rhine-Rhur city Cologne* (optional city walk) in the morning. Marvel at its cathedral, the Gürzenich and the historic Old Town. Enjoy the captain’s gala dinner in the evening.</p>
<p><strong>Day 7</strong> </p>
<p>Today the ship stops in Volendam. The highly recommended ‘Holland Waterland &amp; Amsterdam city tour’ excursion* takes place today, which includes a visit to the small fishing town of Volendam, a trip to Edam with a visit to a Dutch cheese farm and a city tour through Amsterdam which includes a canal cruise. In the afternoon, explore Amsterdam on your own by bike or on foot. Overnight in Amsterdam.</p>
<p><strong>Day 8</strong> </p>
<p>Disembark after breakfast in Amsterdam and transfer to the airport (approx. 20mins) for your return flight to the UK.</p>
<p>Please note: Itinerary subject to change. *Optional excursions are available to pre-book.</p>
<p> </p>
<p class="location-text geolocation-title"> </p>
