<p><strong>PACKAGE A £115:</strong> City tour Strasbourg, city tour Heidelberg, city walk Cologne, excursion Holland Waterland and city tour Amsterdam with canal cruise.</p>
<p><strong>PACKAGE B £157:</strong> City tour Strasbourg, city tour Heidelberg, city walk Rüdesheim with music museum, city walk Cochem with wine tasting, city walk Cologne, excursion Holland Waaterland and city tour Amsterdam with canal cruise.</p>
<p><strong>PACKAGE C £210:</strong> City tour Strasbourg, excursion Alsace and wine, city walk Speyer, city tour Heidelberg, city walk Rüdesheim with music museum, city walk Koblenz, city walk Cochem with wine tasting,  city walk Cologne, excursion Holland Waaterland and city tour Amsterdam with canal cruise.</p>
<p>More details on pre-bookable excursions can be requested by email.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">Detailed itinerary (Amsterdam-Basel)</h2>
<p><strong>Cruise</strong> Amsterdam - Volendam - Cologne - Cochem - Koblenz - Rüdesheim -Mannheim/Heidelberg - Speyer - Strasbourg - Basel</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Day 1 </strong></p>
<p>Fly to Amsterdam, transfer to the ship (approx. 20 mins) and board the Amadeus ship in the late afternoon. Relax with a welcome cocktail and special dinner. Overnight at anchor in Amsterdam.</p>
<p><strong>Day 2 </strong></p>
<p>Take an optional* city tour and canal cruise in Amsterdam or explore the city on your own by foot or bike. After lunch, the Holland Waterland excursion* starts, which includes a visit to a dairy factory in Edam and a stroll through the small fishing town of Volendam. The cruise continues into Germany. </p>
<p><strong>Day 3 </strong></p>
<p>Today the ship docks in the Rhine-Ruhr citiy of Cologne. Marvel at the many landmarks, such as its cathedral, the Gürzenich and the historic Old Town. Guided city tour* available. The ship leaves Cologne after dinner.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4 </strong></p>
<p>The morning is spent enjoying the beautiful Rhine valley scenery floating by. The ship arrives in Cochem after lunch. Explore this quaint medieval town on your own or take a guided walk* which includes a wine tasting session.</p>
<p><strong>Day 5 </strong></p>
<p>Visit Koblenz* (optional walking tour), a 2000-year old town at the junction of the rivers Rhine and Moselle, where picturesque riverside scenery meets an abundance of cultural monuments and historic buildings. Journey through the most beautiful stretch of the Rhine valley today, a UNESCO world heritage site, passing castles and charming villages. Stop in Rüdesheim* in the evening and stroll along the Drosselgasse with its many shops and restaurants. The optional walking tour includes a visit to the music museum.</p>
<p><strong>Day 6 </strong></p>
<p>The ship docks in Mannheim in the morning, which is situated at the confluence of the Rhine and the Neckar. Explore Mannheim or join an optional city tour of Heidelberg*, home of Germany's oldest university. The tour includes a visit to the city's imposing castle, a red sandstone ruin overlooking the Neckar River and a walking tour through the historic old quarter and the market place. After lunch, the ship docks at the old imperial city of Speyer* (optional city walk). In the evening, the Captain welcomes you to a special gala dinner.</p>
<p><strong>Day 7 </strong></p>
<p>Today you arrive in the Alsace region of France, a Unesco World Heritage site. The ship docks in Strasbourg* (optional city tour). </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Day 8</strong></p>
<p>Arrival in Basel and disembark after breakfast. Transfer to Basel airport for your flight back to the UK or transfer to the train station for your rail transfer to one of our Swiss resorts.</p>
<p>Please note: Itinerary subject to change. *Optional excursions are available to pre-book.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Save 15% with our pre-bookable excursion packages:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Pre-bookable Excursion Package for Classical Rhine river cruise Amsterdam-Basel:</strong></p>
<p><strong>PACKAGE A £115:</strong> City tour Amsterdam with canal cruise &amp; Holland Waterland, city walk Cologne, city tour Heidelberg, city tour Strasbourg.</p>
<p><strong>PACKAGE B £157:</strong> City tour Amsterdam with canal cruise &amp; Holland Waterland, city walk Cologne, city walk Cochem with wine tasting, city walk Rüdesheim with music museum, city tour Heidelberg, city tour Strasbourg.</p>
<p><strong>PACKAGE C £210:</strong> City tour Amsterdam with canal cruise &amp; Holland Waterland, city walk Cologne, city walk Cochem with wine tasting, city walk Koblenz, city walk Rüdesheim with music museum, city tour Heidelberg, city walk Speyer, city tour Strasbourg.</p>
<p>More details on pre-bookable excursions can be requested by email.</p>
</div>
